---
title: Tiger Voice Agent - Event-Driven Onboarding Sequence v2.0
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant CDE as Credit Decision Engine
    participant CPS as Customer Profile
    participant KAFKA as Event Bus (Kafka)
    participant SCHEMA as Schema Registry
    participant DEDUP as Idempotency Cache (Redis)
    participant ORC as Orchestration Layer
    participant CE as Compliance Engine
    participant REDIS as Redis Session Store
    participant AGENT as Voice AI Agent (Runtime)
    participant TOOLS as Tool Router + Policy GW
    participant USER as Customer
    participant KYC as KYC Provider
    participant CIS as Card Issuer
    participant CRM as CRM / Sales
    participant NS as Notification System
    participant DLQ as Dead Letter Queue
    participant OBS as Observability (OTel)

    Note over CDE,OBS: STAGE 1: Card Approved (with enhanced event infrastructure)

    CDE->>SCHEMA: Validate card_approved schema
    SCHEMA-->>CDE: Schema valid (v2.1)
    CDE->>KAFKA: card_approved {event_id, customer_id, limit, risk_tier, correlation_id}
    
    KAFKA->>ORC: Consume event
    ORC->>DEDUP: Check event_id in idempotency cache
    DEDUP-->>ORC: NOT_SEEN (first delivery)
    ORC->>DEDUP: Store event_id (7-day TTL)
    
    ORC->>OBS: Start distributed trace (correlation_id)
    ORC->>CPS: Read customer profile (name, phone, lang)
    CPS-->>ORC: Profile data
    ORC->>CRM: Read call history, campaign_source
    CRM-->>ORC: History + campaign data
    
    ORC->>CE: Pre-call check (consent, DND, time window, cooldown)
    CE-->>ORC: CLEARED
    
    Note over ORC: Pre-call state refresh: verify stage hasn't advanced
    ORC->>CPS: Re-read onboarding_stage (final check)
    CPS-->>ORC: stage = EKYC_PENDING (confirmed)
    
    ORC->>REDIS: Store session context {customer_id, stage, variables}
    ORC->>AGENT: Initiate call with EKYC_PENDING flow + system variables (PII masked)
    
    AGENT->>USER: "This is Tara, your AI assistant from Tiger Credit Card. This call is recorded..."
    AGENT->>TOOLS: verify_identity(customer_id, user_response)
    TOOLS->>CE: Policy check (identity verification permitted)
    CE-->>TOOLS: APPROVED
    TOOLS->>CPS: Verify identity data
    CPS-->>TOOLS: VERIFIED
    TOOLS-->>AGENT: verification_status = passed
    
    AGENT->>USER: Congratulations + credit limit + eKYC guidance
    USER-->>AGENT: Response (questions / agreement)
    
    AGENT->>TOOLS: send_sms_link(customer_id, "ekyc_deeplink")
    TOOLS->>CE: Policy check (SMS rate limit)
    CE-->>TOOLS: APPROVED
    TOOLS->>NS: Send SMS with deep link
    NS->>USER: SMS delivered
    
    AGENT->>USER: Benefits summary + closing
    AGENT->>TOOLS: log_disposition(customer_id, "ekyc_link_sent", notes)
    TOOLS->>CRM: Write disposition
    TOOLS->>CE: Write audit log
    
    ORC->>OBS: End trace (call_duration, outcome, latency_metrics)

    Note over CDE,OBS: DUPLICATE EVENT HANDLING

    KAFKA->>ORC: card_approved (REDELIVERED - same event_id)
    ORC->>DEDUP: Check event_id
    DEDUP-->>ORC: ALREADY_SEEN
    ORC->>ORC: Acknowledge and discard (no action)

    Note over CDE,OBS: FAILED EVENT HANDLING

    KAFKA->>ORC: ekyc_completed {event_id, customer_id}
    ORC->>CPS: Read customer profile
    CPS-->>ORC: ERROR 503 (service unavailable)
    ORC->>ORC: Retry 1 (after 1s backoff)
    ORC->>CPS: Read customer profile
    CPS-->>ORC: ERROR 503
    ORC->>ORC: Retry 2 (after 5s backoff)
    ORC->>CPS: Read customer profile
    CPS-->>ORC: ERROR 503
    ORC->>DLQ: Route to Dead Letter Queue {event, error, retry_count: 3}
    ORC->>OBS: Alert: CPS unavailable, event sent to DLQ

    Note over CDE,OBS: RACE CONDITION PREVENTION

    KYC->>KAFKA: ekyc_completed {customer_id}
    KAFKA->>ORC: Consume event
    ORC->>CPS: Read profile
    Note over ORC: 10 minutes pass (call queue delay)
    Note over ORC: Customer completes VKYC independently during wait
    ORC->>CPS: Pre-call state refresh
    CPS-->>ORC: stage = ACTIVATION_PENDING (advanced!)
    ORC->>ORC: Skip VKYC call, check if ACTIVATION_PENDING flow is queued
    ORC->>OBS: Log: stage_skip {from: VKYC_PENDING, to: ACTIVATION_PENDING}
